{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/6081411", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/6081411/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/6081411/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/tag/1.1", "id": 6081411, "author": {"login": "javiersantos", "id": 2229658, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIyMjk2NTg=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2229658?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos", "html_url": "https://github.com/javiersantos", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTYwODE0MTE=", "tag_name": "1.1", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Version 1.1", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2017-04-14T09:15:46Z", "published_at": "2017-04-14T09:23:11Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/tarball/1.1", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/zipball/1.1", "body": "* Fixed a weird crash caused when using the emulator check. You should now pass a boolean to do a deeper check.\r\n\r\n```Java\r\nboolean deep = false;\r\nnew PiracyChecker(this)\r\n\t.enableEmulatorCheck(deep)\r\n\t...\r\n\t.start();\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Note:** the deep boolean with make the library do extra checks to detect if device is an emulator or not. It could lead to some weird crashes, so be wise when using it.\r\n\r\n* Added check for a new pirate apps store: ACMarket.\r\n* Added more things to `destroy()` method just to make sure everything is properly destroyed.\r\n* Added an option to set light or normal status bar for LicenseActivity.\r\n\r\n```Java\r\n.withActivityColors(R.color.colorPrimary, R.color.colorPrimaryDark, withLightStatusBar)\r\n```\r\n\r\n* Added an option to set a custom layout xml for LicenseActivity.\r\n\r\n```Java\r\n.withActivityLayout(R.layout.my_custom_layout)\r\n```\r\n\r\nA huge thanks to @jahirfiquitiva for his contributions to this update."}
{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/5793924", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/5793924/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/5793924/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/tag/1.0.2", "id": 5793924, "author": {"login": "javiersantos", "id": 2229658, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIyMjk2NTg=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2229658?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos", "html_url": "https://github.com/javiersantos", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTU3OTM5MjQ=", "tag_name": "1.0.2", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Version 1.0.2", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2017-03-19T11:24:47Z", "published_at": "2017-03-19T11:32:37Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/tarball/1.0.2", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/zipball/1.0.2", "body": "* Added `.destroy()` to avoid ServiceConnection leaks. See the Wiki for a [sample usage](https://github.com/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/wiki/Using-Google-Play-Licensing-(LVL)).\r\n* Added Toolbar and some customizations to `Display.ACTIVITY`. Use `.withActivityColor(R.color.colorPrimary, R.color.colorPrimaryDark)` to customize the activity with your own colours.\r\n* Added Galaxy Apps Store to InstallerID: `.enableInstallerId(InstallerID.GALAXY_APPS)`.\r\n* #16 Fixed issue when using the emulator check in certain Samsung devices.\r\n* Renamed `blockIfUnauthorizedAppDetected(...)` by `blockIfUnauthorizedAppUninstalled(...)`."}
{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/5731551", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/5731551/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/5731551/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/tag/1.0.1", "id": 5731551, "author": {"login": "javiersantos", "id": 2229658, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIyMjk2NTg=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2229658?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos", "html_url": "https://github.com/javiersantos", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTU3MzE1NTE=", "tag_name": "1.0.1", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Version 1.0.1", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2017-03-13T23:46:55Z", "published_at": "2017-03-13T23:47:13Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/tarball/1.0.1", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/zipball/1.0.1", "body": "Bug fixes.\r\n\r\n--------\r\n\r\n### Sooooo many changes, improvements and new features \ud83c\udf89 \ud83c\udf89 \ud83c\udf89\r\n\r\n* LVL implementation has been updated. This changes should make harder to apply a patch when using piracy apps (aka Lucky Patcher, Freedom, etc).\r\n* You can now display the result of the license checker in a new Activity by using `.display(Display.ACTIVITY)`. This way you make sure that the main activity of the app is finished.\r\n* Unauthorized apps (such as LuckyPatcher, Freedom and CreeHack) are now detected using a new method `.enableUnauthorizedAppsCheck()`. You can even block your app when this pirate apps has been uninstalled. See \"[Verify the use of pirate apps](https://github.com/javiersantos/PiracyChecker#verify-the-use-of-pirate-apps)\" for more details.\r\n* Third-party stores (such as Aptoide, BlackMart, Mobogenie, 1Mobile, GetApk, GetJar and SlideMe) are now detected using a new method `.enableStoresCheck()`.\r\n* Added `.enableDebugCheck()` to check if app is a debug build.\r\n* Added `.enableEmulatorCheck()` to check if app is being run in an emulator.\r\n* Added `.saveResultToSharedPreferences(preferences, preferenceName)` to save the result of the license check in `SharedPreferences`. See the [README](https://github.com/javiersantos/PiracyChecker#save-the-result-of-the-license-check-in-sharedpreferences) for more details.\r\n\r\nA huge thanks to @jahirfiquitiva for his PR \ud83d\udc4f"}
{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/5729106", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/5729106/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/5729106/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/tag/1.0", "id": 5729106, "author": {"login": "javiersantos", "id": 2229658, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIyMjk2NTg=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2229658?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos", "html_url": "https://github.com/javiersantos", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTU3MjkxMDY=", "tag_name": "1.0", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Version 1.0", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2017-03-13T19:34:34Z", "published_at": "2017-03-13T19:50:52Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/tarball/1.0", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/zipball/1.0", "body": "### Sooooo many changes, improvements and new features \ud83c\udf89 \ud83c\udf89 \ud83c\udf89\r\n\r\n* LVL implementation has been updated. This changes should make harder to apply a patch when using piracy apps (aka Lucky Patcher, Freedom, etc).\r\n* You can now display the result of the license checker in a new Activity by using `.display(Display.ACTIVITY)`. This way you make sure that the main activity of the app is finished.\r\n* Unauthorized apps (such as LuckyPatcher, Freedom and CreeHack) are now detected using a new method `.enableUnauthorizedAppsCheck()`. You can even block your app when this pirate apps has been uninstalled. See \"[Verify the use of pirate apps](https://github.com/javiersantos/PiracyChecker#verify-the-use-of-pirate-apps)\" for more details.\r\n* Third-party stores (such as Aptoide, BlackMart, Mobogenie, 1Mobile, GetApk, GetJar and SlideMe) are now detected using a new method `.enableStoresCheck()`.\r\n* Added `.enableDebugCheck()` to check if app is a debug build.\r\n* Added `.enableEmulatorCheck()` to check if app is being run in an emulator.\r\n* Added `.saveResultToSharedPreferences(preferences, preferenceName)` to save the result of the license check in `SharedPreferences`. See the [README](https://github.com/javiersantos/PiracyChecker#save-the-result-of-the-license-check-in-sharedpreferences) for more details.\r\n\r\nA huge thanks to @jahirfiquitiva for his PR \ud83d\udc4f"}
{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/5264742", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/5264742/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/5264742/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/tag/0.0.3", "id": 5264742, "author": {"login": "javiersantos", "id": 2229658, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIyMjk2NTg=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2229658?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos", "html_url": "https://github.com/javiersantos", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTUyNjQ3NDI=", "tag_name": "0.0.3", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Version 0.0.3", "draft": false, "prerelease": true, "created_at": "2017-01-25T15:29:54Z", "published_at": "2017-01-25T16:06:20Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/tarball/0.0.3", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/zipball/0.0.3", "body": "- Updated the code for Google Play Licensing library from their [GitHub site](https://github.com/google/play-licensing/).\n- Added required permission to AndroidManifest.xml\n\n``` xml\n<uses-permission android:name=\"com.android.vending.CHECK_LICENSE\"/>\n```\n- The callback method has been updated to manage license check errors.\n\n``` Java\n.callback(new PiracyCheckerCallback() {\n    @Override\n    public void allow() {\n        // Do something when the user is allowed to use the app\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void dontAllow(PiracyCheckerError error) {\n        // You can either do something specific when the user is not allowed to use the app\n        // Or manage the error, using the 'error' parameter, yourself (Check errors at {@link PiracyCheckerError}).\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void onError(PiracyCheckerError error) {\n        // This method is not required to be implemented/overriden but...\n        // You can either do something specific when an error occurs while checking the license,\n        // Or manage the error, using the 'error' parameter, yourself (Check errors at {@link PiracyCheckerError}).\n    }\n})\n```\n- The minimum API level is now 9 (Gingerbread).\n- Updated ProGuard rules.\n\nHuge thanks to @jahirfiquitiva for his PR #11.\n"}
{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/3326541", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/3326541/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/3326541/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/releases/tag/0.0.2", "id": 3326541, "author": {"login": "javiersantos", "id": 2229658, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIyMjk2NTg=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2229658?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos", "html_url": "https://github.com/javiersantos", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/javiersantos/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTMzMjY1NDE=", "tag_name": "0.0.2", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Version 0.0.2", "draft": false, "prerelease": true, "created_at": "2016-05-28T15:00:12Z", "published_at": "2016-05-28T15:04:58Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/tarball/0.0.2", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/javiersantos/PiracyChecker/zipball/0.0.2", "body": "- Added Amazon App Store: `.enableInstallerId(InstallerID.AMAZON_APP_STORE)`\n- `.enableInstallerId()` now supports multiple installers. For example:\n\n``` Java\n.enableInstallerId(InstallerID.GOOGLE_PLAY)\n.enableInstallerId(InstallerID.AMAZON_APP_STORE)\n```\n- Fixed an issue when comparing the APK signature.\n- Non-LVL checkers will be executed before the LVL checkers, since they are asynchronous and could take some seconds to give a result.\n"}
